DefaultChoiceDisplayText.SourceString: To spread fear among the population.

DefaultChoiceDisplayText.SourceString: They found it too funny. Matching the motive.

DefaultChoiceDisplayText.SourceString: They have a very annoying laugh.

DefaultChoiceDisplayText.SourceString: There are no rabbits in Falador.

DefaultChoiceDisplayText.SourceString: They were drunk, but their story was too detailed.

Message.SourceString: The shrine is damaged, a piece missing. Until it is repaired the magic cannot flow to the village barrier.
Message.LocalizedString: The shrine is damaged, a piece missing. Until it is repaired the magic cannot flow to the village barrier.

Message.SourceString: When the balloons started popping, I just assumed it was another drop party, you know? I figured there was always a chance I could get something from one, like a party hat or something. But they weren't popping because of parties, they were popping because the arrows went flying.
Message.LocalizedString: When the balloons started popping, I just assumed it was another drop party, you know? I figured there was always a chance I could get something from one, like a party hat or something. But they weren't popping because of parties, they were popping because the arrows went flying.

Message.SourceString: The lord of balance leaves his blessing in a harmonious circle, guarded by a dread beast. Obtain the blessings of all the gods to destroy the barrier.
Message.LocalizedString: The lord of balance leaves his blessing in a harmonious circle, guarded by a dread beast. Obtain the blessings of all the gods to destroy the barrier.

Message.SourceString: Sure, in the chaos, I stole a couple of gemstones someone left as they ran. But, i mean, come on, it was a drop party after all! Fair game. I shouldn't have to suffer because of that.
Message.LocalizedString: Sure, in the chaos, I stole a couple of gemstones someone left as they ran. But, i mean, come on, it was a drop party after all! Fair game. I shouldn't have to suffer because of that.

Message.SourceString: The statue no longer maintains the barrier to the village.
Message.LocalizedString: The statue no longer maintains the barrier to the village.

Message.SourceString: Justice must be maintained, even in times of great strife. Seek the wisdom of Armadyl on a nearby lake, where three spirits await judgement.  Obtain the blessings of all the gods to destroy the barrier.
Message.LocalizedString: Justice must be maintained, even in times of great strife. Seek the wisdom of Armadyl on a nearby lake, where three spirits await judgement.  Obtain the blessings of all the gods to destroy the barrier.

Message.SourceString: I'd just been wandering over by the party room, the sound of balloons popping is soothing, you know? I had my bow out, because, well, I thought I could shoot a couple of them that floated away. Balloons, obviously.
Message.LocalizedString: I'd just been wandering over by the party room, the sound of balloons popping is soothing, you know? I had my bow out, because, well, I thought I could shoot a couple of them that floated away. Balloons, obviously.

Message.SourceString: You offer a prayer to the shrine and it hums with magical energy. The barrier around the village weakens.
Message.LocalizedString: You offer a prayer to the shrine and it hums with magical energy. The barrier around the village weakens.

Message.SourceString: Ha! Then the screaming happened, man it was funny!
Message.LocalizedString: Ha! Then the screaming happened, man it was funny!

Message.SourceString: What? Oh, come on, you'd have been laughing too. Balloons exploding as people fell over them running, you can't not laugh at that? It was all "Aaargh *POP* Noooo! *POP* My precious spleen!" how is that not funny?
Message.LocalizedString: What? Oh, come on, you'd have been laughing too. Balloons exploding as people fell over them running, you can't not laugh at that? It was all "Aaargh *POP* Noooo! *POP* My precious spleen!" how is that not funny?

Message.SourceString: So many dead. Falador lined with bodies. But, it wasn't me, honest. I had nothing to do with it. I was just hunting rabbits.
Message.LocalizedString: So many dead. Falador lined with bodies. But, it wasn't me, honest. I had nothing to do with it. I was just hunting rabbits.

Message.SourceString: You offer a prayer to the shrine, and it hums with magical power. The barrier around Emberwood village weakens as a result.

Message.SourceString: Cast your verdict arbiter. What crime was committed?
Message.LocalizedString: Cast your verdict arbiter. What crime was committed?

Message.SourceString: Incorrect. An arbiter must not be so blind to the crimes committed. Speak to the spirits again to learn the true crime committed.
Message.LocalizedString: Incorrect. An arbiter must not be so blind to the crimes committed. Speak to the spirits again to learn the true crime committed.

Message.SourceString: Indeed, a brutal and terrible crime. Many lives lost in an instant, their families deprived of their loved ones. Tell me, why was such an act committed?
Message.LocalizedString: Indeed, a brutal and terrible crime. Many lives lost in an instant, their families deprived of their loved ones. Tell me, why was such an act committed?

Message.SourceString: Incorrect. An arbiter must not be so blind to the crimes committed. Speak to the spirits again to learn the true crime committed.
Message.LocalizedString: Incorrect. An arbiter must not be so blind to the crimes committed. Speak to the spirits again to learn the true crime committed.

Message.SourceString: Saradomin shields this village from the relentless dead. Seek his power on high, surrounded by a ring of water. Obtain the blessings of all the gods to destroy the barrier.
Message.LocalizedString: Saradomin shields this village from the relentless dead. Seek his power on high, surrounded by a ring of water. Obtain the blessings of all the gods to destroy the barrier.

Message.SourceString: Yes. Imagine, an act of such violence, such tragedy and loss. Families ruined. Destinies upended. Futures shattered. All because someone found it amusing. As though the lives of others carry no more weight than an ant beneath ones boot. But, tell me, who committed the crime?
Message.LocalizedString: Yes. Imagine, an act of such violence, such tragedy and loss. Families ruined. Destinies upended. Futures shattered. All because someone found it amusing. As though the lives of others carry no more weight than an ant beneath ones boot. But, tell me, who committed the crime?

Message.SourceString: I shouldn't be here. I deserve to move on! I was there, sure, when the bodies piled up, but I had nothing to do with it. It was a sunny day, the light was in my eyes and there were rabbits everywhere and I just thought, why not? You know? There's good eating on one of those.
Message.LocalizedString: I shouldn't be here. I deserve to move on! I was there, sure, when the bodies piled up, but I had nothing to do with it. It was a sunny day, the light was in my eyes and there were rabbits everywhere and I just thought, why not? You know? There's good eating on one of those.

Message.SourceString: I never get invited to parties, but this house party was something special, you know? A great achievement, deserving of celebration, how could I turn it down? We laughed, we drank, we danced the night away, it was wonderful. Partying till morning, in the glare of the sun.
Message.LocalizedString: I never get invited to parties, but this house party was something special, you know? A great achievement, deserving of celebration, how could I turn it down? We laughed, we drank, we danced the night away, it was wonderful. Partying till morning, in the glare of the sun.

Message.SourceString: It was a lovely house party, really it was. But, the weather was cold and grey, and I just wanted to go for a walk, you know? So that's why I was there, in the park, when  the trouble started.
Message.LocalizedString: It was a lovely house party, really it was. But, the weather was cold and grey, and I just wanted to go for a walk, you know? So that's why I was there, in the park, when  the trouble started.

Message.SourceString: We thought we might end celebrations at the Party Room, you know? Balloons, prizes, everyone having the time of their lives? Sure, we were a bit drunk, but who wouldn't be after an all night rager?
Message.LocalizedString: We thought we might end celebrations at the Party Room, you know? Balloons, prizes, everyone having the time of their lives? Sure, we were a bit drunk, but who wouldn't be after an all night rager?

Message.SourceString: Justice must prevail, for the barrier to rise. Such is the will of Armadyl. Long ago a terrible act was committed. What was the crime? Who is responsible and why did they do it? Name these and unlock the blessing of Armadyl.
Message.LocalizedString: Justice must prevail, for the barrier to rise. Such is the will of Armadyl. Long ago a terrible act was committed. What was the crime? Who is responsible and why did they do it? Name these and unlock the blessing of Armadyl.

Message.SourceString: An interesting deduction, but an incorrect one. Speak to the spirits once more and look for the discrepancies in their tales.
Message.LocalizedString: An interesting deduction, but an incorrect one. Speak to the spirits once more and look for the discrepancies in their tales.

Message.SourceString: Speak to the ghosts to learn their take on the events. Look for the discrepancies and the emotions at play, the guilty often trap themselves with their own lies.
Message.LocalizedString: Speak to the ghosts to learn their take on the events. Look for the discrepancies and the emotions at play, the guilty often trap themselves with their own lies.

Message.SourceString: Yes, the guilty often miss the smaller details as they try to pretend their innocence. This spirit was responsible for the destruction and will pay the price in the afterlife.
Message.LocalizedString: Yes, the guilty often miss the smaller details as they try to pretend their innocence. This spirit was responsible for the destruction and will pay the price in the afterlife.

Message.SourceString: Yes. Sometimes the guilty lack shame, or remorse, unable to keep their strange sense of pride hidden. To them, this massacre was an amusement, a bit of a laugh. To others, it was the worst day of their lives... or their last.
Message.LocalizedString: Yes. Sometimes the guilty lack shame, or remorse, unable to keep their strange sense of pride hidden. To them, this massacre was an amusement, a bit of a laugh. To others, it was the worst day of their lives... or their last.

Message.SourceString: So, I took a shot, even though the glare made it hard to see and, well, next thing I know there's screaming. I ran, I admit it. I ran from the city gate, all the way to the party room. I figured music and revelry would keep me safe, right?

Message.SourceString: The power of chaos wards this village form harm. Hail Zamorak! Seek his altar near by, where the suffering is strongest. Obtain the blessings of all the gods to destroy the barrier.
Message.LocalizedString: The power of chaos wards this village form harm. Hail Zamorak! Seek his altar near by, where the suffering is strongest. Obtain the blessings of all the gods to destroy the barrier.

Message.SourceString: I think it was the laughing that came first. Loud and obnoxious, a guffawing cackle that we heard over the screaming. They thought it was funny, as they tore the city apart. Laughing as they went.
Message.LocalizedString: I think it was the laughing that came first. Loud and obnoxious, a guffawing cackle that we heard over the screaming. They thought it was funny, as they tore the city apart. Laughing as they went.
